  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nCurrently we have `forge install` and `forge remove` — we're mixing up conventions and this is a little smelly.\r\n\r\nI'd recommend we move to one of the following, based on conventions set up by other package managers:\r\n\r\n1. `forge add` and `forge remove`\r\n2. `forge install` and `forge uninstall`\r\n\r\nFor example, `yarn` uses `add` and `remove`. `npm`, `pip`, and `gem` use `install` and `uninstall`.\r\n\r\nI like `add`/`remove` because there's less to type, but I can see the case being made for `install`/`uninstall`.\r\n\r\nBackwards compatibility is definitely a concern.\r\n\r\nCurious what people's thoughts are here!\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
